    "department": "Marketing",
    "description": "LIFE AT UIPATH\n\nThe people at UiPath believe in the transformative power of automation to change how the world works. We’re committed to creating category-leading enterprise software that unleashes that power.\n\nTo make that happen, we need people who are curious, self-propelled, generous, and genuine. People who love being part of a fast-moving, fast-thinking growth company. And people who care—about each other, about UiPath, and about our larger purpose.\n\nCould that be you?\n\nOverview of areas of activities for a Social Media \u0026 Content working student in Central Europe, as part of the Central Europe Marketing team\n\nCE = Central Europe (Germany, Austria, Switzerland, Liechtenstein)\n\nOverview of activities – Social media \u0026 content working student Central Europe Marketing\n\nThe working student supports the Central Europe Marketing team with a focus on Social Media, content localization and campaign execution.\n\nThe role is hands-on and operational, working closely with regional marketing managers and selected internal stakeholders to support visibility, awareness and campaign execution in the region\n\nThe role offers hands-on experience across core B2B marketing activities in a global AI \u0026 Automation SaaS environment.\n\nThis is what you'll do at UiPath\n\nSocial Media\n\nActively support social media activities for UiPath in the CE region with a focus on LinkedIn.\n\nTasks include:\n\n - Support selected regional leaders with social media content ideation and planning and light content creation for LinkedIn – no full profile management\n\n - Help draft and create social media content such as texts, carousels, short video formats in close alignment with marketing plans for different media (LinkedIn, YouTube, different formats…)\n\n - Prepare and provide content for the Employee Advocacy platform to promote campaigns, events, PR and content assets\n\n - Maintain a simple social media content overview/calendar\n\n - Coordinate content inputs and approvals with regional marketing stakeholders\n\n - Track and report basic performance metrics (e.g., reach, engagement, clicks)\n\nContent \u0026 Localization\n\nSupport the localization and adaptation of global marketing content for the Central European market.\n\nTasks include:\n\n - Review translated global campaign assets (landing pages, social posts, customer assets) for language quality, clarity and local relevance\n\n - Suggest adjustments to reflect regional context, messaging and tone better\n\n - Support creation of additional regional content elements where required (e.g. short copy, social snippets, campaign supporting posts)\n\nWeb Content Support\n\nSupport content updates and regional web content maintenance in collaboration with global teams.\n\nTasks include:\n\n - Update and maintain content on uipath.com/de http://uipath.com/de based on defined guidelines and instructions\n\n - Perform first-level content reviews before publishing\n\n - Coordinate content changes with internal stakeholders (e.g., marketing, web team)\n\nCampaign \u0026 Paid Media Support\n\nSupport regional and global campaigns with a focus on execution and content preparation.\n\nTasks include:\n\n - Assist with execution of integrated marketing campaigns across channels (web, email, paid, social, events)\n\n - Support preparation and adaptation of creative assets for paid digital campaigns\n\n - Coordinate inputs and feedback with internal digital marketing and campaign teams\n\n - Help track campaign activities, deliverables and timelines\n\nReporting \u0026 Analytics\n\nSupport reporting and transparency across ongoing social media activities.\n\nTasks include:\n\n - Prepare simple reports and status updates for social media and campaigns\n\n - Collect performance data and present results in a structured format\n\n - Support the team with ad-hoc reporting and analyses as needed\n\nWhat you'll bring to UiPath\n\n - Enrolled student in Marketing, Communications, Media, Business or a related field\n\n - Excellent written and verbal communication skills in German and English; French is a plus\n\n - Knowledge and experience with B2B Social Media, especially LinkedIn Communication and capable of writing posts for the region leaders and for employee advocacy\n\n - Digital Marketing knowledge, preferably B2B\n\n - Self-organized, structured, reliable and accountable working style\n\n - Strong interest in digital tools and B2B technologies\n\n - First experience with Hootsuite, CMS, Marketo, Salesforce, Adobe Creative Cloud \u0026 Document\n\n - Cloud, AI tools; Intent data tools like 6sense are a plus\n\nMaybe you don’t tick all the boxes above—but still think you’d be great for the job? Go ahead, apply anyway. Please. Because we know that experience comes in all shapes and sizes—and passion can’t be learned.\n\nMany of our roles allow for flexibility in when and where work gets done. Depending on the needs of the business and the role, the number of hybrid, office-based, and remote workers will vary from team to team. Applications are assessed on a rolling basis and there is no fixed deadline for this requisition. The application window may change depending on the volume of applications received or may close immediately if a qualified candidate is selected.\n\nWe value a range of diverse backgrounds, experiences and ideas. We pride ourselves on our diversity and inclusive workplace that provides equal opportunities to all persons regardless of age, race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, and expression, national origin, disability, neurodiversity, military and/or veteran status, or any other protected classes. Additionally, UiPath provides reasonable accommodations for candidates on request and respects applicants' privacy rights. To review these and other legal disclosures, visit our privacy policy https://www.uipath.com/legal/trust-and-security/privacy-policy.",
